The paper discusses research in the area of Web mining, which involves techniques from several research communities, including database, information retrieval, natural language processing, and machine learning. Therefore, it is likely to be classified under cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.DB (Databases), cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). However, since the paper focuses on representation issues, the process, learning algorithms, and applications, it is more likely to be classified under cs.IR and cs.DB, followed by cs.CL, cs.AI, and cs.LG.
